          "abstract": "Educational development is an extended academic field worldwide with a diverse knowledge base to reflect the multi-disciplinarity of academic developers. Many developers want to share their contributions in educational development and research, but find the process of writing and publishing unclear. In this session we will create a collaborative space in which we can share experiences on this process with ICED’s peer-reviewed International Journal for Academic Development. The editors will answer your questions about writing, researching, reviewing, and publishing in the field of academic development. The editors will focus in particular on how to make your work appropriate for and appealing to an international audience.",
