          "title": "When AI Becomes a Colleague: Academic Developer Agency in AI Governance",
          "authors": "Jannette Flores",
          "presenter": "",
          "abstract": "The rapid expansion of AI tools in higher education is creating new pressures for academic developers, who are increasingly called upon to guide faculty, reassure leadership, and maintain student trust without clear institutional frameworks. This Collaborative Space introduces the Learning Integrity Trust (LIT) Framework, a conceptual model designed to help academic developers articulate, negotiate, and strengthen institutional agency in the age of generative AI. Rather than a traditional presentation, the session invites participants to interrogate, refine, and extend the LIT Framework in relation to their own systems, constraints, and priorities. Through structured dialogue and small group work, participants will examine how faculty, student, and institutional agency are shaped by AI practices and emerging governance structures. The session aims to surface shared challenges, context specific adaptations, and potential collaborations, supporting academic developers who are working at the intersection of educational practice, policy, and institutional strategy.",
